snippet.textDisplay:
The world is a community and if you want to welcome somebody with open arms, then don't mock somebody's ignorance. Sure, it may not be a "song" but a qawwali. When somebody praises the singer and calls the art a "song", just be happy that people of other culture and background want to be a part of this community.
Also, a simple definition of a song is "When a singer draws words melodiously paired up with music/tune". And this qawwali totally fulfills this definition of a Song. Don't try to be Word Nazi (if that is even a word).
And it is an awesome qawwali indeed.
